    "name": "Shortly - URL Shortener API",
    "description": "# Shortly - URL Shortener API\n\nProduction-ready URL shortening service with Redis caching and comprehensive analytics.\n\n## üåê Environments\n\nThis collection includes two environments:\n\n**Production** (Railway)\n\n- Base URL: [https://shortly-prod.up.railway.app](https://shortly-prod.up.railway.app)\n    \n- Ready to use immediately\n    \n\n**Local** (Development)\n\n- Base URL: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)\n    \n- Requires local setup (see GitHub repo)\n    \n\n## üîë Authentication\n\nAll API endpoints require an API key passed via header:\n\n```\nX-API-Key: your_api_key_here\n\n ```\n\n**Demo API Keys:**\n\n- `demo_api_key_1_yck908xhjhvx1mzyj4qrxux6rup4ay4q3ebx37ui9h1gad4jw` (1000 req/hr)\n    \n- `demo_api_key_2_t0rr4xh8ktniiwvpdymqvhwme054bj49d33p6r4gidm3rf6rt` (100 req/hr)\n    \n\n## üìñ Quick Start\n\n1. Select **Production** environment (top-right dropdown)\n    \n2. Go to **URL Operations** folder\n    \n3. Run **\"Create Short URL (Basic)\"** request\n    \n4. Copy the `shortCode` from response\n    \n5. Test redirect by visiting: [https://shortly-prod.up.railway.app/{shortCode}](https://shortly-prod.up.railway.app/%7BshortCode%7D)\n    \n6. View analytics: Run **\"Get URL Analytics\"** request\n    \n\n## üîó Links\n\n- **Live Demo:** [https://shortly-prod.up.railway.app](https://shortly-prod.up.railway.app)\n    \n- **GitHub:** [https://github.com/yourusername/url-shortener](https://github.com/yourusername/url-shortener)\n    \n- **Documentation:** See README.md in repository\n    \n\n## ‚ö° Features\n\n- Fast redirects (<100ms cached)\n    \n- Rate limiting (per API key)\n    \n- Custom URL aliases\n    \n- Expiry dates\n    \n- Comprehensive analytics",
